## 🚀 Run / Rebuild

```bash
bash ./scripts/rebuild-and-restart.sh                 # Debug build, production API
bash ./scripts/rebuild-and-restart.sh --development   # currently a no-op (flag parsed but never used; no scheme/endpoint switch)
bash ./scripts/rebuild-and-restart.sh --app-store     # App Store scheme
```

- `--app-store` builds the **separate** `WhisperShortcut-AppStore` target, which defines the `APP_STORE` compilation condition. Gate App-Store-only behavior with `#if APP_STORE` (e.g. the Accessibility-free Dictate Prompt and the removed auto-paste / selection Read Aloud required for Guideline 2.4.5); the direct/GitHub build keeps the full feature set.

## 🔗 Gemini API / models

When working with **Gemini models** (transcription, prompt mode, TTS, model IDs, or API issues):

- Use the official Gemini API documentation: <https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs>
- Always verify current model IDs using official docs and the **llm-model-docs** skill (canonical for Gemini, OpenAI, and xAI).
- Regularly check the **Google AI Developers Forum** for outages, deprecations, and known issues: <https://discuss.ai.google.dev/c/gemini-api/4>

## 📁 Data Directories

WhisperShortcut uses one canonical app data location so sandboxed and non-sandboxed builds share the same files:

- `~/Library/Containers/com.magnusgoedde.whispershortcut/Data/Library/Application Support/WhisperShortcut/`

When debugging, resetting, or counting interaction logs, check this canonical path. See `WhisperShortcut/Docs/data-directories.md` for details.

